description: For sale: $435,000. A RARE find on 1.80 acres! This "YEAR ROUND" home has 200 feet of frontage on Rose Lake with easy water and private boat launch access! The private Lake features white sand and clear, spring fed water! This "LAKE LIVING" home has room for an addition if you desire, and is perfectly set up for easy water access, parties and carefree living!  Custom built in 1990, this contemporary 3 Bdrm, 3 Bath home + a cozy guest cabin is a great investment.  The house boasts an open floor plan with upper level bedrooms, balcony and sitting room, lower level living, kitchen, dining, and bedroom areas. There is a soaring 2 1/2 story natural stone fireplace and the property was designed with a friendly concept for entertaining.  Perfect for a getaway on an overcast or sunny day, as an added bonus space, there is a sun room that extends the width of the home with views. The oversized attached 3+ car heated garage has a stall for a RV or boat, storage areas and also a 3/4 Bath.  (Also included in this acreage is an addnl lot across the Rd.)  Buy in 2020 and you can enjoy watching wildlife, feeding the birds, a trek in the woods, boating, water sports, fishing, hiking, biking and ski trails just out your door!

Large 25x40 garden surrounded by electric fence containing a cedar pergola for shade and well-established blueberries, grapes, asparagus, and multiple fruit trees. Pollinators welcome with beekeeping area on backside of garden. Pond in front includes small island filled with perennials and bridge across to visit and feed the ducks. Large barn with upper loft ideal for a hobby farm or storage, previously housed horses. Newly paved driveway.
